Package: robinhood-lustre
Section: admin
Architecture: amd64
Priority: optional
Conflicts: robinhood-posix
Provides: robinhood
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, lustre-client-utils (>= 2.11)
Description: Robinhood Policy Engine for Lustre filesystems
 Robinhood is a tool for monitoring and applying policies to file system
 entries.  It is designed to process all its tasks in parallel, so it is
 particularly adapted for managing large file systems with millions of
 entries and petabytes of data.
 .
 This package contains Robinhood for Lustre file systems. If you need
 Robinhood for Posix file systems, use robinhood-posix instead.

