 Robinhood is a tool for monitoring and applying policies to file system
 entries.  It is designed to process all its tasks in parallel, so it is
 particularly adapted for managing large file systems with millions of
 entries and petabytes of data.
 .
 This package contains Robinhood for Posix file systems. If you need
 Robinhood for Lustre file systems, use robinhood-lustre instead.

Package: robinhood-adm
Section: admin
Architecture: amd64
Priority: optional
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: admin/config helper for Robinhood PolicyEngine
 Robinhood is a tool for monitoring and applying policies to file system
 entries.  It is designed to process all its tasks in parallel, so it is
 particularly adapted for managing large file systems with millions of
 entries and petabytes of data.
 .
 This package provides an admin/config helper for Robinhood PolicyEngine
 (command rbh-config).

Package: robinhood-webgui
Section: admin
Architecture: amd64
Priority: optional
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Web interface to vizualize filesystems stats from Robinhood
 Robinhood is a tool for monitoring and applying policies to file system
 entries.  It is designed to process all its tasks in parallel, so it is
 particularly adapted for managing large file systems with millions of
 entries and petabytes of data.
 .
 This uses Robinhood database to display misc. user and group stats.

Package: robinhood-test
Section: admin
Architecture: amd64
Priority: optional
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, robinhood, robinhood-adm, bc
Description: Test suite for Robinhood
 Robinhood is a tool for monitoring and applying policies to file system
 entries.  It is designed to process all its tasks in parallel, so it is
 particularly adapted for managing large file systems with millions of
 entries and petabytes of data.
 .
 This package contains Lustre and Posix tests for Robinhood.

